entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: An open-source AI operating system project. It involves CLI functionality, custom plugins, and integration with various AI models and platforms.

entities.name: Eliza Labs
entities.description: The organization behind the ElizaOS project. They are involved in legal disputes and development of the AI system.

entities.name: X Corp
entities.description: A social media platform formerly known as Twitter. It is currently in a legal dispute with Eliza Labs over account suspension and API access fees.

entities.name: Gemini
entities.description: An AI model or service, also referred to as 'Nano Banana,' that can be used for image editing and creation. It is offered for free.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform for version control and collaboration, primarily used for software development. It hosts code repositories and manages pull requests.

entities.name: Ani
entities.description: A community-launched token created to fund legal action against X/Elon.

entities.name: Shaw
entities.description: A key individual associated with Eliza Labs and the ElizaOS project, involved in legal actions and public statements.

entities.name: Baoskee
entities.description: A community member who launched the 'Ani' token to support legal action against X/Elon.

entities.name: DaosFun
entities.description: A platform or organization associated with Baoskee, involved in launching the 'Ani' token.

entities.name: Dr. Neuro
entities.description: A community member who suggested using Gemini for image editing tasks.

entities.name: Grok
entities.description: An AI model or service, potentially associated with X Corp, mentioned in discussions about ElizaOS and open-source AI.

entities.name: Jin
entities.description: A community member who advocated for ElizaOS to complement Grok rather than compete with it.

entities.name: New York Times
entities.description: A major newspaper and news media organization that is planning an interview with Shaw regarding the situation with X Corp.

entities.name: Composio
entities.description: A tool or system designed to address limitations in MCPs by enriching them with metadata for tool dependency graph generation.

entities.name: EDDY
entities.description: A cryptocurrency token discussed by users in the context of ElizaOS and potential platform fee revenues.

entities.name: ELI5
entities.description: A cryptocurrency token discussed by users in the context of ElizaOS.

entities.name: Sonnet 4
entities.description: A version or component related to AI models, noted for its ability to handle a 1 million token context length.

entities.name: EU
entities.description: The European Union, a political and economic union of member states. Its Digital Markets Act (DMA) is being considered as a legal avenue against X Corp.

entities.name: x402
entities.description: A product from Coinbase suggested for stablecoin payments for AI services, potentially used in hackathons.

entities.name: Coinbase
entities.description: A cryptocurrency exchange platform that offers the x402 product for stablecoin payments.

entities.name: Python
entities.description: A high-level, interpreted, general-purpose programming language known for its readability and extensive libraries.

entities.name: Unity
entities.description: A cross-platform game engine and framework used for developing interactive content, including speech and language processing systems.

entities.name: TypeScript
entities.description: A typed superset of JavaScript that compiles to plain JavaScript. It is being considered for porting systems to ElizaOS.

entities.name: Apple
entities.description: A technology company that is developing an AI SDK which may be integrated with ElizaOS.

entities.name: React Native
entities.description: A framework for building native mobile applications using React. It is considered for potential integration with ElizaOS.

entities.name: SQLite
entities.description: A C-language library that implements a small, fast, self-contained, high-reliability, full-featured, SQL database engine. It may be integrated with ElizaOS.

entities.name: pglite
entities.description: A WebAssembly port of SQLite, designed for efficient database operations within web environments. It may be integrated with ElizaOS.

entities.name: Elon
entities.description: An individual, likely Elon Musk, who is the subject of legal action initiated by Eliza Labs, alongside X/Twitter.
